<a name="details" id="details"></a><h2 class="groupheader">Detailed Description</h2>
<div class="textblock"><p><a class="el" href="classsf_1_1Mutex.php" title="Mutex defines a mutex (MUTual EXclusion) object, that allows a thread to lock critical instructions t...">Mutex</a> defines a mutex (MUTual EXclusion) object, that allows a thread to lock critical instructions to avoid simultaneous access with other threads. </p>
<p>The Win32 version uses critical sections, as it is faster than mutexes.<br/>
 See <a class="el" href="classsf_1_1Lock.php" title="Lock is an exception-safe automatic wrapper for locking and unlocking mutexes.">Lock</a> for an efficient way of using it. </p>

